# Miracle Coins CoinSync Pro - Cursor Rules

## TypeScript Requirements
- **MANDATORY**: All code must use TypeScript with strict type checking
- **MANDATORY**: All API responses must be properly typed
- **MANDATORY**: All form data must use Zod schemas for validation
- **MANDATORY**: All database models must have corresponding TypeScript interfaces
- **MANDATORY**: All function parameters and return types must be explicitly typed
- **MANDATORY**: Use enums for all status fields and constants
- **MANDATORY**: All API calls must use typed response interfaces

## Code Quality Standards
- **MANDATORY**: Use ESLint and Prettier for code formatting
- **MANDATORY**: All components must be functional components with TypeScript
- **MANDATORY**: Use React Query for all API state management
- **MANDATORY**: Implement proper error boundaries and loading states
- **MANDATORY**: All user inputs must be validated with Zod schemas
- **MANDATORY**: Use proper TypeScript generics for reusable components

## Backend Standards
- **MANDATORY**: All endpoints must use Pydantic models for request/response validation
- **MANDATORY**: All database operations must use typed repositories
- **MANDATORY**: All business logic must be in service classes
- **MANDATORY**: All API responses must follow consistent error handling patterns
- **MANDATORY**: All database models must use SQLAlchemy with proper typing
- **MANDATORY**: All async operations must be properly handled with try/catch

## Testing Requirements
- **MANDATORY**: All new features must have corresponding tests
- **MANDATORY**: Test coverage must be above 80%
- **MANDATORY**: All API endpoints must have integration tests
- **MANDATORY**: All business logic must have unit tests
- **MANDATORY**: All TypeScript types must be tested for correctness

## AI Integration Standards
- **MANDATORY**: All AI evaluations must return typed responses
- **MANDATORY**: AI confidence scores must be properly validated
- **MANDATORY**: All AI suggestions must be logged for audit purposes
- **MANDATORY**: AI evaluation results must be stored with proper typing

## Security Standards
- **MANDATORY**: All admin routes must verify JWT tokens
- **MANDATORY**: All file uploads must be validated and typed
- **MANDATORY**: All user inputs must be sanitized
- **MANDATORY**: All database queries must use parameterized statements

## Performance Standards
- **MANDATORY**: All database queries must be optimized
- **MANDATORY**: All API responses must be paginated when appropriate
- **MANDATORY**: All images must be properly optimized
- **MANDATORY**: All API calls must have proper loading states

## Documentation Standards
- **MANDATORY**: All TypeScript interfaces must be documented
- **MANDATORY**: All API endpoints must have OpenAPI documentation
- **MANDATORY**: All complex business logic must be commented
- **MANDATORY**: All AI evaluation logic must be documented

## File Organization
- **MANDATORY**: All types must be in `/types` directory
- **MANDATORY**: All API calls must be in `/lib/api.ts`
- **MANDATORY**: All components must be in `/components` directory
- **MANDATORY**: All hooks must be in `/hooks` directory
- **MANDATORY**: All utilities must be in `/utils` directory

## Error Handling
- **MANDATORY**: All errors must be properly typed
- **MANDATORY**: All API errors must be handled gracefully
- **MANDATORY**: All form validation errors must be user-friendly
- **MANDATORY**: All network errors must have retry logic

## Accessibility Standards
- **MANDATORY**: All form inputs must have proper labels
- **MANDATORY**: All images must have alt text
- **MANDATORY**: All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- **MANDATORY**: All color contrasts must meet WCAG standards

## Professional UI Standards
- **MANDATORY**: All modals must be properly centered and responsive
- **MANDATORY**: All loading states must have proper animations
- **MANDATORY**: All success/error messages must be clearly visible
- **MANDATORY**: All forms must have proper validation feedback
- **MANDATORY**: All tables must be sortable and filterable
- **MANDATORY**: All buttons must have proper hover states
- **MANDATORY**: All inputs must have focus states
- **MANDATORY**: All cards must have proper shadows and borders

## AI Evaluation Standards
- **MANDATORY**: All AI evaluations must show confidence scores
- **MANDATORY**: All AI suggestions must be explainable
- **MANDATORY**: All AI results must be actionable
- **MANDATORY**: All AI evaluations must be logged for improvement

## Collection Management
- **MANDATORY**: All collections must be properly typed
- **MANDATORY**: All collection operations must be validated
- **MANDATORY**: All collection data must be properly structured
- **MANDATORY**: All collection APIs must be RESTful

## Deployment Standards
- **MANDATORY**: All environment variables must be properly typed
- **MANDATORY**: All configuration must be validated at startup
- **MANDATORY**: All database migrations must be tested
- **MANDATORY**: All API versions must be properly documented

## Monitoring Standards
- **MANDATORY**: All API calls must be logged
- **MANDATORY**: All errors must be tracked
- **MANDATORY**: All performance metrics must be monitored
- **MANDATORY**: All user actions must be audited




